h. Now available for the first time in paperback, it describes in non-technical language what he discovered in a lifetime of study about honeybees--their methods of orientation, their sensory faculties, and their remarkable ability to communicate with one another. Thomas Seeley's new foreword traces the revolutionary effects of von Frisch's work, not just for the study of bees, but for all subsequent research in animal behavior. This new paperback edition also includes an "Appreciation" of von Frisch by the distinguished biologist Martin Lindauer, who was Frisch's protégé and later his colleague and friend.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAbeille. 0aEtologia Animal. 0aInsetos Em Geral (Biologia). 0aTiere (Zoologie). 4aAnimal communication. 4aAnimal orientation. 4aBees. 4aInsects -- Behavior. 4aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aChadwick, Leigh E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeeley, Thomas D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Science eBook Packagez9783110353549oZDB-23-HSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067441876940uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067441877640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674418776423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674418776/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HSP